<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1601,1989]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1601,1628]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[312,396,1602,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1082,1107]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,166,1062]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[173,1414,166,1062]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Records of Ischnura heterosticta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342283/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). This taxon is recorded from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[815,924,1602,1628]" name="Indonesia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1020,1602,1628]" name="Palau" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Palau</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1145,1603,1629]" name="Tonga" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Tonga</collectingCountry>
, including all of mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[151,254,1638,1664]" name="Australia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[308,419,1638,1664]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[459,635,1638,1665]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, it has been recorded from more than 50 localities, including ultramafic substrates, on which it is abundant. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bigot, L." box="[546,688,1673,1700]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="317 - 329" refId="ref31010" refString="Bigot, L. (1985) Contribution a l'etude des peuplements littoraux et cotiers de la Nouvelle-Caledonie (Grand Terre, Ile des Pins) et d'une des iles Loyaute (Ouvea): premier inventaire entomologique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 21, 317 - 329." type="journal article" year="1985">Bigot (1985)</bibRefCitation>
recorded several individuals from Ouvéa. Several individuals from Anse Vata in Nouméa, Pont Pérignon (Parc Provincial de la Rivière Bleue) and Montagne des Sources (
<date box="[1298,1428,1710,1737]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1963-12-30">30/12/1963</date>
) are also held in the 
<collectionCode box="[370,449,1746,1772]" country="New Caledonia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crvj-94ys" name="Office de la Recherche Scientifique et Technique d'Outre-Mer" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">ONNC</collectionCode>
collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1601,1989]" box="[199,1014,1781,1809]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1781,1808]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[305,543,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Ischnura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heterosticta">
<emphasis box="[305,543,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ischnura heterosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1877" box="[597,731,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Agriocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsudans">
<emphasis box="[597,731,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. exsudans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
often occur syntopically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1601,1989]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,473,1817,1844]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Biology and behaviour.</emphasis>
The larva was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hawking, J." box="[788,975,1818,1845]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref32835" refString="Hawking, J. (1986) Dragonfly larvae of the river Murray system. A preliminary guide to the identification of know final instar odonate larvae of south-eastern Australia. Albury- Wodonga Development Corporation, Technical report, No. 6, 1 - 65." type="book chapter" year="1986">Hawking (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. Its behaviour is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brauer" authorityYear="1865" box="[1330,1429,1819,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Ischnura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurora">
<emphasis box="[1330,1429,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">I. aurora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Charpentier, 1840" authorityName="Charpentier" authorityYear="1840" box="[151,463,1854,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Ischnura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,251,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ischnura</emphasis>
Charpentier, 1840
</taxonomicName>
species are highly aggressive, it is not uncommon to see 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1127,1283,1854,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Ischnura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heterosticta">
<emphasis box="[1127,1283,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">I. heterosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
catching and eating individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1877" box="[388,522,1890,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Agriocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsudans">
<emphasis box="[388,522,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. exsudans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1601,1989]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,281,1925,1952]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Status.</emphasis>
According to its wide regional distribution, including 
<collectingCountry box="[883,1057,1926,1953]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, we do not consider 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1283,1436,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Ischnura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heterosticta">
<emphasis box="[1283,1436,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">I. heterosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as threatened and rank it as LC.
</paragraph>
